    "title": "All We Know, Is But A Page",
    "description": "&quot;In periods of economic upheaval, in periods of economic crisis, wealth is not destroyed, it is merely transferred.&quot;\n– Larry Bates, in &quot;The Money Masters: How International Bankers Gained Control of America&quot; (1998).\n\nSaid the little Eohippus,\n&quot;I am going to be a horse,\nAnd on my middle fingernails\nTo run my earthly course!\n* * *\nI'm going to have a flowing tail!\nI'm going to have a mane!\nI'm going to stand fourteen hands high\nOn the Psychozoic plain!&quot;\n– Charlotte P. S. Gilman, &quot;Similar Cases&quot;",
